Independent schools in Scotland maintain a reputation for academic excellence, continuing in 2018 with another excellent performance of test results, which is only reinforced by individual and collective achievements in sports, the arts, music and other social sciences.
With up to 30,000 pupils across Scotland, these schools, represented by the Scottish Independent Schools Association (SCIS), aim to provide the best possible standard for their pupils and their parents.
Independent schools aim to prepare their students for further education, their chosen careers and their place in a global world.
As an education sector that can create and implement personal curricula, we see that modern languages continue to be a popular and desirable subject in schools.
Nelson Mandela said, "If you talk to someone in a language they understand, your words can reach them.
But if you speak his own language, you touch his heart.
