Germany has again delayed the launch of a new warship.
The newest frigate of the German fleet was to be commissioned in 2014 to replace the outdated Cold War warships, but this will not happen until at least the following year due to poor systems and skyrocketing costs, local media reported.
The commissioning of the Rheinland-Pfalz, the flagship of the brand's new Baden-Wuerttemberg-class frigates, has been postponed until the first half of 2019, according to Die Zeit, which quoted an army spokesman.
